     "Recurrent laryngeal nerve (branch of vagus) innervates all laryngeal muscles except cricothyroid. Unilateral injury → hoarseness. Bilateral injury → stridor, respiratory distress — airway emergency. Superior laryngeal supplies cricothyroid.",
